&lt;p&gt;# Comments: 3&lt;/p&gt;</description><guid isPermaLink="false">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47919725</guid><pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 10:14:15 +0000</pubDate></item><item><title>Ask HN: AI is like a hyper-motivated 16-year old genius – how to manage?</title><link>https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=47919719</link><description>&lt;p&gt;A while ago I posted a comment regarding AI being like a genius 16year old - extrem knowledgeable in technical details, hyper-motivated, feels a need to help. But no production experience, no instinct on what might cause catastrophic issues in that very environment.&lt;p&gt;So what would you do with such an individual who has the potential to be of great help with current issues?&lt;p&gt;- not let him touch production systems at all
- always have someone experienced looking over his shoulder (hoping she/he is fast enough to prevent issues)?
- restrict credentials and give only access to a sandbox?
- only explain the dangers you see and make use of his knowledge but otherwise just hope for the best (and trust your recovery plans)?&lt;p&gt;I see many similarities between AI and this teenager - do you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
